Visualizing Land Cover Maps
The Mkoani district encompasses the southern region of Pemba Island and represents a critical area for marine spatial planning integration. The land cover comparison between 2020 and 2021 reveals the baseline conditions and any changes occurring within the first year of the planning initiative. Understanding what happens on land is essential to marine planning because terrestrial land use directly influences coastal water quality, sediment loading, nutrient runoff, and ultimately the health of nearshore marine ecosystems. Forest cover provides watershed protection and reduces erosion, while agricultural expansion can increase sedimentation in coastal waters. The temporal comparison allows us to track whether land use changes are occurring and at what rate, informing both terrestrial and marine management strategies.


